<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">What is the skill lvl I need to have my reasearch at in order to make that lvl spells? I.E. lvl 34 spells do I need to have my skill at 110?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">PhyzzleMage</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Great question!.  Please, if anyone has an answer or even an experienced guess this would be very useful.  Just failed making my 29 Earth pet AGAIN!.  I'm at 31 with research training maxed.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Reptanis</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Let me qualify this with the fact I do not know at what skill level, various spells are "trivial".<P>This most likely works like trade skills. To have even a slight chance to succed, you would need to have your research skill maxed at the level of spell you are making. A total _rough_ guess:<BR>20% chance at entry spell circle level.<BR>50% chance at next spell circle skill level.<BR>80% chance at +2 spell circle level.<P>So, take a level 24 spell. With research skill maxed at level 24 cap:<BR>- you have a 20% chance to make a level 24 spell.<BR>- you have a 50% chance to make a level 20 spell.<BR>- you have a 80% chance to make a level 16 spell.<P>I'm sure this in not accurate, only gives you an idea. Also note that spell research starts lower and stays lower than most skills.<BR>Most are (lvl X 5) + 5 = skill cap.<BR>Research is (lvl X 5) - 65 = skill cap.<P>So, even though one might be 24th level and have research skill "maxed", it is still only a skil of 55, with a 55's sucess rate.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well thank you for the response  <IMG SRC="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/ubb/smile.gif"> I was finally able to make my lvl 34 spells with a skill of 115.  at that skill lvl all of the lvl 29 spells were trivial but i still failed at some of them but that could be attrubited to my wisdom being low hehe (int is 201 now) I am now lvl 41 and my reasearch skill is 125(havent trained fully in it yet). I havent been able to find all my runes for 39spells yet so as soon as i do I will be back and post on it.  <BR>My main reason for wondering what the skill cap is, is that i really do not want to fail when I finally try to make my ice comet spell. I want to be maxed on my training.<P>Stina Bomberina Bomberina<BR>lvl 41 Wizard GNOME!!!!<BR>Vazehelle</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#FFFFFF"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Stina</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Just an update  <IMG SRC="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/ubb/smile.gif"> my Research Skill is now 170 and the lvl 44 gravity flux spell is trivial.  I have just hit lvl 49 and i havent dared try to make the lvl 49 research spells yet  <IMG SRC="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/ubb/frown.gif"> I have reduced myself to buying the IC spell though(sorry) But I do Plan on Making it anyhow  <IMG SRC="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/ubb/smile.gif"> also once again I still have never done any of the research quests and just put all  my points into research I alway use up all my runes i have for that lvl before I put my training points in around skill 165 it costs about 50pp per point and gets expensive hehe BUT hey WE are Wizards!! so if you need cash just go kill Hill giants and make about 300 to 400pp an hour  <IMG SRC="http://mythiran.allakhazam.com/ubb/tongue.gif"><P>Stina Bomberina Bomberina<BR>lvl 49 Wizard GNOME!!!!<BR>Officer of Celestae </FO